  <section class="intro-section container">
    <div class="intro-content">
      <h2>True Refrigeration Repair in Southern California — What's Actually At Stake</h2>

      <p>True Refrigeration has been manufacturing commercial refrigerators and freezers in Springfield, Missouri since 1945. They are the most widely deployed commercial refrigerator brand in American food service — the T-49 two-door reach-in is to restaurant kitchens what a Toyota Camry is to American roads. Walk into virtually any independent restaurant in Los Angeles and you'll find a True reach-in, a True undercounter, or a True prep table. The brand's market penetration in SoCal's food service ecosystem means we service True equipment every single day.</p>

      <p>What makes True different from most commercial refrigeration brands — and what makes proper repair matter more — is the engineering investment in each unit. True's foamed-in-place polyurethane insulation is bonded to the cabinet structure, not inserted as a panel. Their fan motors are rated for 15–20 years of service. The cam-lift hinge system on their reach-in doors is designed to close on a 1/8-inch clearance to minimize cold air loss. None of this matters if the defrost system isn't working, the condenser coils are loaded with restaurant grease, or the door gaskets have worn out from 200 daily open-close cycles.</p>

      <p>When a True unit fails during dinner service, the immediate cost is real and quantifiable. A T-49 two-door reach-in holds roughly $2,000–$4,000 of protein, dairy, and produce in a typical restaurant. A failure on a Friday afternoon before a busy weekend can result in a total loss of that inventory plus a scramble for emergency restocking. We treat True commercial calls as exactly what they are — revenue-critical equipment failures that need same-day resolution.</p>

      <p>EPA 608 certified. R-290 qualified for current True models running propane refrigerant. $120 commercial diagnostic applied to the repair. Call {phone}.</p>
    </div>

    <aside class="sticky-cta-box">
      <p class="scb-brand">True Refrigeration</p>
      <p class="scb-phone">{phone}</p>
      <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn btn-primary btn-block">Emergency Call</a>
